</code>
                    </pre>

                    <!-- Configuring PostCSS -->
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-display mb-2 mt-6">
                        Configuring PostCSS
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-center">
                        Update your <code>postcss.config.js</code> file:
                    </p>
                    <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-js">
// postcss.config.js
module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
};
</code>
                    </pre>

                    <!-- Building and Compiling CSS -->
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-display mb-2 mt-6">
                        Building and Compiling CSS
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-center">
                        Add the Tailwind directives to your CSS file (e.g., <code>wwwroot/css/site.css</code>):
                    </p>
                    <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-css">
&commat;tailwind base;
&commat; components;
&commat; utilities;
</code>
                    </pre>
                    <p class="text-center mt-4">
                        Then, build your CSS by running:
                    </p>
                    <pre class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg mt-2 overflow-auto text-sm md:text-base">
<code class="language-bash">
npx tailwindcss -i ./wwwroot/css/site.css -o ./wwwroot/css/output.css --watch
</code>
                    </pre>

                    <!-- Automating with Build Scripts -->
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-display mb-2 mt-6">
                        Automating with Build Scripts
